doc.after: Liverpool s local rail network is one of the busiest and most extensive in the country The network consists of three lines the Northern Line which runs to Southport Ormskirk Kirkby and Hunts Cross the Wirral Line which runs through the Mersey Railway Tunnel and has branches to New Brighton West Kirby Chester and Ellesmere Port and the City Line which begins at Lime Street providing links to St Helens Wigan Preston Warrington and Manchester
